Terminal commands:

ls -a    # to see all files, including hidden files
cat (and name of file, [tab to complete name]) to see text inside that file

pwd  # to see directory being worked.

mkdir  # make a new directory

**  PROCESS **
git pull
git status
git add .   ( to add all files)
git commit -m "message"
git status
git push

how to hide?

put the path in quotes when using cd
"C:\Users\Haydn\Documents\QA Work\QA Automation"

Git Branches
git branch -av  // list local and remote branches.
                    * indicates current branch

git branch newbranch // creates new branch 'newbranch'

git checkout newbranch // switches to 'newbranch'

git checkout -b newbranch2 // creates and moves into 'newbranch2'

git branch -d newbranch // deletes 'newbranch'

git merge newbranch2 // merges newbranch2 items to current branch

Create file and put data inside, one command
echo "this is text" > test3.txt

cat test3.txt // to see contents



